| Model/controller tests | 🔲 Pending |
| GUI | 🔲 Planned |

## Building and Running

From the `src/` directory:

```bash
chmod +x build.sh   # first time only
./build.sh
```

The script cleans any previous compilation, compiles all source files into `bin/`, and launches the program. If compilation fails, it stops and reports the error without attempting to run.

**Requirements:** Java 17 or higher.

## Project Structure

```
project/
├── src/
│   ├── build.sh
│   ├── main/           # Source files
│   └── test/           # Test files (mirrors main/)
└── bin/                # Compiled .class files (generated)
```

